			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Hard coal, also known as anthracite, is a hard natural coal that burns slowly and gives intense heat. It contains greater potential to produce heat energy than softer, geologically newer coal. Anthracite is incredibly scarce and is the most brittle among coal types. When burned, it produces a very hot, blue flame. It is used primarily for heating residential and commercial buildings.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">硬煤又称无烟煤，是一种坚硬的天然煤，燃烧缓慢，发热量大。与地质构造较新、质地较软的煤炭相比，它具有更大的热能生产潜力。无烟煤非常稀少，是煤炭中最脆的一种。燃烧时会产生非常热的蓝色火焰。它主要用于住宅和商业建筑的供暖。</common:generalComment>
